history.content: I think you will be fine, granted you do spend the time to make up for whatever you’re missing from 61C. The content for 162 itself isn’t too difficult to follow — it’s the projects.

children.subject: Also depends on what you struggled on 61C. There is some overlap, but not a lot.

You should be fine. I got a C+ in 61C and ended up with a B+ in 162. I didn't do particularly well on midterms 1 and 3, and did pretty bad on midterm 2. Like Mudit said, it really comes down to the projects.

For me, I view the class as being split into three parts: midterm 1 (threads and synchronization), 2 (virtual memory, paging and scheduling), and 3 material (file systems and other random things). Midterm 2 material is very much 61C flavor, and if you did well in 61C then you will most likely do well in midterm 2. If you did not do well in 61C that does not really imply you will do bad in midterm 2! The other two midterms are pretty much completely new topics, very different from 61C.

I think what determines your grade for the most part in this class is your midterm scores. The midterms are tricky and long, more so than other classes. Make sure to study hard for those and take them seriously!

history.content: I enrolled in 162 for the Spring semester because it seems like a useful class. I didn't do so hot in 61C (like below a B) and I don't think I absorbed all that much from it; am I screwed for 162 or will I be able to make up for my not-great 61C knowledge during the semester?
history.subject: How hard is 162 if I did badly in 61C?
